node.text:
Spotting sea snakes with @brodiemoss: “Sea snakes normally avoid humans but this time of year they become very active, sexually frustrated and potentially aggressive as they search for a mate 🐍 like this old fella who appeared from the ocean floor and followed me around on my paddle board before disappearing 😅”

What would you do in this situation? 😱

📽 @brodiemoss #nature
📍Australia

node.text:
Taking care of a turtle at the @ogasawara_marine_centre, a nonprofit organization dedicated to the environmental conservation and protect green turtles and other marine creatures in Ogasawara, Japan. 🐢

Why turtle cleaning is done? 🧼
A build up of algae and other waste can lead to skin disease so it’s important that we clean their shells often!
The brown and green on the turtles are a mix of algae and water scales. ***This turtle is being cleaned at a marine rescue centre / do not try this!! In the wild this is done by cleaner fish 🐟

The "Turtle Center" takes in and rehabilitates ill or injured sea turtles, and helps raise young turtles from eggs to their release into the wild @nature. It's nestled in the Ogasawara Islands, also known as The Bonin Islands, a World Natural Heritage Site and an archipelago of over 30 subtropical and tropical islands in Micronesia, located around 1,000 kilometres south of Tokyo. 🇯🇵

Tag someone who loves and want to take care of @nature 💙

📽 @ryuta_og @ogasawara_marine_centre #nature
📍 Ogasawara Islands, Japan
🎶 Makana - Glow Of The Moon

node.text:
Letting the locals show you around! 💦 Kayaking the crystal clear waters of Weeki Wachee Springs State Park in Florida is such a blast. You can get approached by some curious manatees along the way. This is one of our top things to do in Florida. There are many places to see manatees in Florida and this is one of our top picks!

A first magnitude spring run that flows 7 miles from its start to where it empties into the Gulf of Mexico. The beauty of the Weeki Wachee starts with the powerful spring, which has such a large flow of crystalline water that it replaces the water in the river every 60 minutes, making the water spectacularly clear and clean. You can see manatees at any point along the Weeki Wachee; sometimes there are manatees right at the springhead.

Did you know that a manatee calf can stay with its mother for up to two years? ☺️

📽 @getupandgoweekiwachee #nature
📍 Weeki Wachee Springs State Park, Florida
🎶 Ludovico Einaudi - Divenire

Midnight sun in Iceland with @h0rdur 🇮🇸☀️ The midnight sun is a natural phenomenon that happens north of the Arctic Circle and south of the Antarctic Circle every summer. In these areas the sun is visible for the entire day, or a consecutive 24-hour span of sunlight. The sun remains visible at the local time of midnight.

In Iceland, the highest peak in the daylight period is called Sumarsólstöður or Summer Solstice and always take place from the 20th of June to the 22nd. So the midnight sun stays visible for more than 21 hours in Reykjavík in the middle of summer. Although the is at it highest point in June, there are bright nights from early May and as late as July. 

The daylight in Iceland is from mid-May to mid-August and the sun only sets for around 3 hours per day, and there is effectively light for the whole 24-hour period. In midwinter, there are around 5 hours of effective daylight.

Tag someone you'd like to experience this @nature phenomenon with! 🌞

📽 @h0rdur #nature
📍Iceland
🎶 Sarah Cothran, Wuki - As the World Caves In (Wuki Remix)
